6 Stopping Applications
***********************

Eventually, an application has to be closed.  The following functions
will properly close one or more running applications, leaving a clean
environment.

 -- Function: cheerilee-close-application window
     Closes the application running inside WINDOW.

     WINDOW is the ID given by the X server to the X window.  Every
     element has this ID saved inside the 'frame' property.  You can
     access this value with 'oref' or 'slot-value' (*note
     (eieio)Accessing Slots::).

 -- Function: cheerilee-close-absolutely-everything
     Disconnects Emacs from the X server.

     Since the connection is closed, any running application is
     automatically closed, and any allocated resource is freed from
     memory.


